  "prompt": "How much time does HSBC take to provide offer letter?",
  "response": "The time it takes for HSBC to provide an offer letter can vary depending on several factors, including the type of position, the specific hiring process for that role, and how quickly the hiring team moves through their review and decision-making processes. Generally, candidates may receive an offer letter anywhere from a few days to a few weeks after the final interview. \n\nIf you are waiting for an offer letter, it is reasonable to follow up with your recruiter or hiring manager for updates.",
